Perfect. Your root structure is already correct:
MULTILLMCOUNCIL/

├── frontend/
├── backend/
├── README.md
├── backend.doc
└── ContextWindow.doc
Now the biggest mistake React developers make is creating folders based on file type instead of features.
Don't do this:
src/

├── components/
│   ├── Button.tsx
│   ├── Chat.tsx
│   ├── Message.tsx
│   ├── Sidebar.tsx
│   └── ...
│
├── hooks/
├── services/
├── utils/
After 2 months you'll have 100 files in components.

Architecture I Recommend
src
src/

├── app/
│
├── features/
│
├── shared/
│
├── pages/
│
├── services/
│
├── store/
│
├── types/
│
├── App.tsx
└── main.tsx

app/
Application-wide setup.
app/

├── router.tsx
├── providers.tsx
└── constants.ts
Examples:
* React Router
* Theme provider
* Global configs

features/
This is where 90% of code lives.
features/

├── chat/
│
├── conversation/
│
├── models/
│
├── memory/
│
└── settings/
Each feature owns everything related to itself.

chat feature
features/chat/

├── components/
│   ├── ChatInput.tsx
│   ├── ChatWindow.tsx
│   └── MessageBubble.tsx
│
├── hooks/
│   └── useChat.ts
│
├── api/
│   └── chatApi.ts
│
├── types/
│   └── chat.types.ts
│
└── index.ts
Everything chat-related stays here.

conversation feature
features/conversation/

├── components/
│   ├── ConversationList.tsx
│   └── ConversationItem.tsx
│
├── api/
│   └── conversationApi.ts
│
├── types/
│   └── conversation.types.ts
│
└── index.ts

models feature
For AI model selection.
features/models/

├── components/
│   ├── ModelSelector.tsx
│   └── ModelBadge.tsx
│
├── data/
│   └── models.ts
│
└── index.ts

shared/
Reusable things.
shared/

├── ui/
│   ├── Button.tsx
│   ├── Input.tsx
│   ├── Modal.tsx
│   └── Card.tsx
│
├── hooks/
│
├── utils/
│
└── lib/
Only truly reusable components go here.

pages/
pages/

├── ChatPage.tsx
├── SettingsPage.tsx
└── NotFoundPage.tsx
Pages compose features.

services/
External integrations.
services/

├── axios.ts
└── api.ts

store/
Zustand.
store/

├── chatStore.ts
├── conversationStore.ts
└── modelStore.ts

types/
Global types.
types/

├── message.ts
├── conversation.ts
└── api.ts

Initial UI Structure
For the first version:
ChatPage

├── Sidebar
│
├── ChatWindow
│
├── MessageBubble
│
├── ChatInput
│
└── ModelSelector
Visually:
┌────────────┬─────────────────────┐
│            │                     │
│ Sidebar    │ Chat Messages       │
│            │                     │
│            │                     │
├────────────┼─────────────────────┤
│            │ Chat Input          │
└────────────┴─────────────────────┘

One Important Rule
For LLM Council:
Never let components talk directly to APIs.
Bad:
ChatInput
  -> fetch()
Good:
ChatInput
    ↓
chatStore
    ↓
chatApi
    ↓
backend
This becomes extremely important once:
* streaming responses
* multiple models
* memory retrieval
* file uploads
are added.

If I were building this tomorrow, I'd first create:
src/

app/
features/chat/
features/conversation/
features/models/
shared/ui/
pages/
store/
services/
types/
and then build only:
1. Sidebar
2. ChatWindow
3. ChatInput
4. ModelSelector